#From the #1085 meta-list: Entrapment Maneuver (no symptom given).
#Target attacking player sacrifices an attacker; you get toughness-X
#Soldier tokens. Uses the ability-granted-to-player machinery.
# https://github.com/WagicProject/wagic/issues/1085
[INIT]
SECONDMAIN
[PLAYER1]
inplay:gold myr,copper myr,silver myr,leaden myr
hand:entrapment maneuver
offerinterruptonphase:attackers
[PLAYER2]
inplay:grizzly bears
[DO]
goto attackers
grizzly bears
yes
gold myr
copper myr
silver myr
leaden myr
entrapment maneuver
choice 0
endinterruption
goto end
goto end
[ASSERT]
ENDOFTURN
[PLAYER1]
inplay:gold myr,copper myr,silver myr,leaden myr,*,*
graveyard:entrapment maneuver
[PLAYER2]
graveyard:grizzly bears
[END]
#RE-MAPPED 2026-06-11 (post 24 engine rounds): the cast NEVER STACKS -
#'yes' on the offerinterruptonphase:attackers window produces no visible
#window, the myr clicks land but no cast follows the entrapment click
#(no 'Action added to stack'), and the granted-picker choice 0s find no
#menu. This is the documented 'opponent's-combat instant-cast harness
#gap' (also referenced from world_at_war's old park): interrupting at
#the opponent's ATTACK DECLARATION is not drivable - the counter-
#interrupt vocabulary interrupts STACK items, and an attack declaration
#stacks nothing. F-family / harness meta-round material, not a card
#bug. When castable, the remaining drive is known: choice 0 (mode) /
#choice 0 (granted picker's must-may) / attacker click (tc-owner
#handover routes P2's pick), per the watchers/notaTarget protocol.
